name: Resume and Portfolio
description: Resume and portfolio of Ian Logan Wesson, currently seeking full-time employment as a graphics software engineer.
html:
Ian Logan Wesson's Resume

Computer scientist looking for a job.
Passionate about graphics software engineering.

Phone: +1-850-345-4333 (USA)
Email: CrazedCoding@gmail.com

Experience

CrazedCoding.com LLC, October 2019 - Current

On contract with the okTurtles Foundation, I am assisting (part-time) in the creation and visualization of essential front and back end algorithms for a project (currently) called Group Income. The project is almost complete.
  • The project GitHub - https://github.com/okTurtles/group-income
  • Project home page - https://groupincome.org/

Graduate Student at Beijing Institute of Technology, September 2018 - September 2020

Earned my Master's in Computer Science and Technology from Beijing Institute of Technology after receiving the Chinese Government Scholarship.
  • Thesis - https://github.com/CrazedCoding/CrazedCoding.com/blob/master/www/thesis-doc-code/Master%20Degree%20Thesis%20of%20Ian%20Wesson.pdf
  • Thesis project defense video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z1HLFvvoKEk
  • Other publications - https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Ian-Wesson

Software Developer at PATLive, February 2012 - February 2013

Initiated efforts to create OpenRCC (a REST API written in Erlang and embedded in OpenACD as a plugin) and OpenCCV (a visual debugger for OpenACD). Developed applications using Java, Erlang, JOGL, and Java WebStart. Communicated with back-end servers to provide real-time updated information. Created a new and innovative integrated content management system.
  • https://github.com/vexevexev/OpenCCV - OpenCCV GitHub repository.
  • https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QkLUHnKV2-c - OpenCCV YouTube demo video.

Bachelor of Science (B.S.), Computer Science, Minors in Mathematics / Physics, 2011 - 2015

I studied Computer Science at FSU for five (5) years, mostly as a part-time student.

  • My personal system for web technologies research and development - https://scienceordie.com
  • YouTube portfolio examples of WebGL/OpenGL projects - https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCDAkHLa83yN5dNWXjokGeEA/videos
  • My shadertoy.com profile (used for WebGL / UI experiments) - https://www.shadertoy.com/user/zovox
  • My (latest) github profile - https://github.com/CrazedCoding/
